HEADWORD: Masterwort
<hw>Mas"ter*wort`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A tall and coarse European umbelliferous plant
(<spn>Peucedanum Ostruthium</spn>, formerly
<spn>Imperatoria</spn>).</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The <spn>Astrantia
major</spn>, a European umbelliferous plant with a showy colored
involucre.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>Improperly, the <altname>cow
parsnip</altname> (<spn>Heracleum lanatum</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mastery</ent>⟦br⟧
